rComments: This prof genuinely brings me joy and makes me want to come to class. Clearly passionate about what he's teaching, and while he doesn't use PowerPoint he keeps me engaged in the lectures with the subtle jokes he cracks.

Hes such a lovely professor. i had him for two courses this semester. an adorable old man, He does do alot of group assignments and presentations. Hes a fair grader as long as you do your work. he's very nice and i respect him! Im happy to be in two of his courses. he does take attendance for each class.

Professor Rickwood should not be teaching online courses. He does not know how to set up Powerpoints, struggles to run Zoom and NEVER answers emails. His lectures rarely follow the content set out in the syllabus and the assigned readings are different than what he teaches. He may be better in person, but I would not recommend for online courses.
Very caring professor, does get lost in lectures but knows a lot about what he's teaching and is easily accessible outside of class

I honestly don't know how this man has such a high rating on this thing. He's a useless lecturer, tests on things that are not discussed/not always highlighted in the readings, he wastes time in class talking about the colour shirt that students are wearing, etc. He's a waste of time, and I learned nothing in his class.

Ive had Rickwood for 3 classes and hes such a funny guy. Really easy going, lots of group work, and easy to do well in his class. He doesnt have powerpoints, or a structure to his class, but hes so funny you can sit back and enjoy his class and get a pretty decent grade. I would take another class with rickwood!

Sweet, caring, and knowledgeable professor. Doesn't stay on topic in the course, doesn't go over much in class either but as long as you understand the key concepts he brings up in class you should do well. Essay-heavy, 1 group presentation. Typical design of a 3rd year public admin course.
Very funny and fun guy.

Easily best teacher I've ever had. Any single one of his classes should be called "Banter Batreps". Essentially, the classes consist of tangents and on-going call outs to the student body. Aside from his hilarious tangents that are the sole good part of this course, he teaches very clearly and very well. Attend class and enjoy the circus show.

Honestly, if there wasn't an attendance sheet, I wouldn't have gone to class. I can definitely say I didn't learn anything at any of his lectures. The textbook was interesting though. He prepares you for the midterm/final by giving you the essay question.

Roger is a class act and hilarious. Even though he does tend to ramble on in class, he's an extremely intelligent person and cares about his students. He tells you what you need to do to pass, and the writing assignment, presentation and exams are pretty straight forward and fair.

Great person, moderate lecturer. His lectures don't have a structure and sometimes ramble a little too much. But show up, participate a bit, do the group work, do the assignments, and you're golden. Fairly low maintenance class. Try really hard to get his attention on the first class, and you will be his favorite student all semester long. #ARTA

Rickwood is such a sweet professor, he really cares about his students. He is generally an easy marker. While he might be reaching the end of career and you might have to, as a class, keep him on track, he is a great prof.
Rickwood is a Saint! Show up and make sure he knows your name! A- guaranteed!

Rickwood is one of the few profs who deeply cares about his students. He does everything he can to help you understand the material and is extremely knowledgable! Although the format of the class is somewhat unstructured it is based on a clear and organized plan included in the syllabus. He is an adorable and caring man, what a gem!
You have to pay attention, but if you do it is well worth it. Prof. Rickwood knows public administration from the field and the library, and is good at balancing academic and practical applications.
Confusing, hard to follow, disorganised. Cynical and long overdue for retirement.
Really nice prof, really helpful

He's a very friendly and endearing prof. The course seemed a little unorganized and the marking scheme was a tad unclear at times. He's incredible intelligent and knowledgeable. He can lecture the entire class without referring to notes, drawing on contemporary examples to consolidate your learning. I'd sign up for another of his classes.

This teacher is extremely friendly and helpful but the class is AWFUL completely unorganized felt more like a history class than a public admin class. He barely follows the texts books and i drowned myself in the textbook because i could never understand him in class. If you ask questions and make yourself noticeable it will help your grade better.

Adorable prof. Seems a little confused most of the time and the class is very unorganized/has no structure at all. Assignments are clear and he is very helpful. Would recommend him just because he is so funny and nice.

This prof is so unorganized, its insane. He never gives your exams on time and he changes the format of the assignment less than 12hrs before. We learn more about law than actually public management. VERY UNORGANIZED! If you want a clear, organized teacher than dont take his class. Aside from that he's a nice guy, who wants to help but ....
Excellent Prof. Care about his students success. Most down to earth prof at University of Ottawa
The most helpful prof ever had. He really tries to ensure students succeed. Had him for a summer class and although some of the MC questions were tricky, he still gives overall good mark.

He was attentive and helpful in answering ALL of his student's questions; regarding not only the course, but graduate application information for schools. He was very thorough in his knowledge about the course, and if you do your required amount of work, he is a fair marker. One of the BEST professor's in regards to the welfare of his student's.
Mediocre prof - very kind and wants the students to succeed, however no structure whatsoever to his classes and the evaluations do not reflect the work done in class.

Such a great prof. Still in his course but is by far one of the most down-to-earth, funniest professors I have ever had. He is very clear about what will be on exams and what he expects from assignments. He makes time to answer your questions and genuinely cares about his students. DEFINITELY RECOMMEND THIS COURSE OR ANY COURSE WITH THIS PROFESSOR
